Anonymous Sun 16 Jul 2023 04:04:23 No.58050742 Report
Quoted By:
>>58047065
>How's the next chapter coming?
I'm currently trying to complete the first draft of a 125k word novel (the words are all done, just needs a lots of retroactive edits and plot readjustments to be consistent). If it it's the one thing I'm doing this year, it's finishing it.
>Planning a new story?
Fighting off the the urge to write other works. I desperately want to write something new and I am actively suppressing that desire.
>Why did you choose this character?
Because I wanted to explore the idea of a ancient mythic warrior working with a modern secret agent in a setting where WW2 era tech meets magic and monsters.
>What's something you want to improve?
I want to improve my prose, I feel it's a bit lifeless and I want to make if feel more alive.
>What's something you want to see others improve?
For this general, I want to see more interesting/better human protags. Everyone talks about the waifur, but I feel authors here forget the human part of /hmofa/. And while there are some good humans, there are plenty who are forgetful, boring or downright unlikeable (and not in the 'love to hate' good way).

There's my rant, have a dragon.

>How's the next chapter coming?
It's coming along well, deaths in the family makes for an emotional rollercoaster and my characters are already going through a lot with a separation so it's going to be interesting pushing them to a level of grief and despair very few people even hear about.

>Planning a new story?
Got two new ones in the book; a troubled American Yakuza duo trying to keep their clan alive in the States while balancing a simple love life and a wolf pack tale surrounding one newly appointed lieutenant and his transitional process of taking on new responsibility within an increasingly notable pack. Both are still on the outline phases but they'll get their dues soon, certainly won't be as gargantuan as my first project. Or they might, I unno, I underestimate my love for writing a lot.

>Why did you choose this character?
For the primary story, I chose them because I grew up an isolated only child and wanted to get lost in a world where I could feel like I had someone to grow up with.
For Shark story and Tiger story, I liked the concept design for sharks and someone urged me to make content for it since I liked it so much, so I did (started to, at least, still a wip). The tiger character looked cute and spunky and seemed to scream a name at me, then I found the artist hadn't come up with a name so I started working up plans for a story for her, then a few days ago I find that she's been given the name I had in mind for her (Esmerelda) so now I just gotta write.

The Yakuza and Wolf stories: I like the idea of troubled characters fighting through difficulties and uncertainties to create the lives they want for them and theirs, and the two characters are in the perfect positions for that being smack in the middle ranks of dangerous and litigious groups.

>What's something you want to improve?
I wanna improve my self perception of my ability and affinity for writing.

>What's something you want to see others improve?
I wanna see anons write mo'
